    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-10-22T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-10-22T13:00:00-05:00" n="282"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d282">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320/10–2253: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The United States Representative at the United Nations</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_LODGEHCJ1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lodge</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-10-22T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 22, 1953—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 150. Re ILC elections.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Delegation suggests Department reconsider present position (<gloss
                            target="#t_GADel1">Gadel</gloss> 36) which is to support <persName>Myint
                            Thein</persName> (Burma) rather than <persName corresp="#p_KHOMANT1"
                            >Khoman</persName> (Thailand). Reasons are: (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>)
                        Thailand supports US in <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> far more
                        consistently than does Burma; (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) We have not
                        supported Thailand for any other post during session; (<hi rend="italic"
                            >c</hi>) Even though <persName>Myint Thein</persName> appears better
                        qualified, <persName corresp="#p_KHOMANT1">Khoman</persName> appears possess
                        necessary qualifications.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>
                        <persName>De La Colina</persName> (Mexico) informs <gloss
                            target="#t_USGADel1">USGADel</gloss> that <gloss target="#t_LAs1"
                            >LA</gloss> delegates do not intend caucus on ILC slate. Only agreement
                        is decision by four states now represented on ILC (Panama, Mexico, Brazil,
                        Colombia) to vote for each other. US therefore free vote for four <gloss
                            target="#t_LAs1">LA</gloss> nominees we consider most highly
                        qualified.</item>
                </list>
                <p>Request Department’s views.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LODGEHCJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lodge</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
